column3: Plant shut down for inspection.  Brazos took all 45,000 for these days.
Plant shut down.  Transition crack in Turbine.   45,000 was sold off to markets during.  Tufco, waha, some transported
on Lonestar for these days.  Plant will be up for rest of year.
Scheduled outage cancelled because the plant came down last week.
Turbine breaks down at 1:30 am.  No gas burning until at least 11/16.  All gas needs to be sold to avoid adding length to
Plant ran at full capactiy producing 263 megawatts per day.  Brazos did not pull any gas during this time.  Upon invesigation
it turns out that several plants in the area are out, causing Cleburne to pick up the slack.
Plant now only burning about 30,000 per day to make power.  Weather cool, but not so cold where power is needed for heat.
